:: StoryStylesheet [stylesheet]
body {
  background: #fff;
  color: #000;
  font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
}
.legos-card, .legos-data {
  border: 2px solid #000;
  padding: 0.8rem;
  margin: 0.8rem 0;
  background: #fff;
}
.legos-data {
  white-space: pre-wrap;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
}
.past { border-left: 8px solid #777; padding-left: 0.6rem; }
.present { border-left: 8px solid #000; padding-left: 0.6rem; }
.future { border-left: 8px solid #c8a800; padding-left: 0.6rem; }
.nav a { font-weight: 700; }

/* ---- BEFLIX integration ---- */
.beflix-stage {
  border: 2px solid #000;
  margin: 0.8rem 0;
  padding: 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  background: #fff;
}
.beflix-stage canvas {
  display: block;
  image-rendering: pixelated;
  image-rendering: crisp-edges;
  background: #fff;
  width: 100%;
  max-width: 512px;
  height: auto;
}
.beflix-bar {
  width: 100%;
  border-top: 2px solid #000;
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 0;
}
.beflix-bar button {
  flex: 1 1 auto;
  min-width: 70px;
  font-family: ui-monospace, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
  font-size: 0.72rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-weight: 700;
  background: #fff;
  color: #000;
  border: none;
  border-right: 2px solid #000;
  padding: 0.45rem 0.3rem;
  cursor: pointer;
}
.beflix-bar button:last-child { border-right: none; }
.beflix-bar button:hover { background: #000; color: #fff; }
.beflix-bar button[data-on="1"] { background: #000; color: #fff; }
.beflix-cap {
  width: 100%;
  border-top: 1px solid #000;
  font-size: 0.66rem;
  letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  opacity: 0.7;
  padding: 0.35rem 0.5rem;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}
.beflix-code {
  width: 100%;
  border-top: 1px solid #000;
  font-size: 0.66rem;
  line-height: 1.4;
  white-space: pre-wrap;
  word-break: break-word;
  padding: 0.4rem 0.5rem;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  background: #fff;
}
.beflix-code .c { opacity: 0.5; }
.beflix-code .k { font-weight: 700; }

:: StoryJavaScript [script]
/* ============================================================
   ZORK · BEFLIX-128  —  embedded interpreter + routine library
   Lives once in StoryJavaScript; every SU passage renders through it.

   A state unit declares a BEFLIX PROGRAM (a function of the live state
   axes). The same program renders every state of its rooms — empty,
   blocked, cleared, dark, thief-passing — by reading the axes, not by
   storing baked frames. This is the Engine Contract, executable.

   COST DISCIPLINE baked in:
     HOT primitives (passage/rock/lampcone/figure/glint) -> min prims
     HEAVY plates (round_room/aragain/hades/dam)          -> full detail
     round_room                                           -> CACHED
     lampcone                                             -> the leverage routine
   ============================================================ */
(function(){
  "use strict";
  var W = 128, H = 96, IMAX = 7;

  /* ---- the shared grid + a per-render cost meter ---- */
  var grid = new Uint8Array(W*H);
  var COST = {}, STACK = [];
  function enter(n){ STACK.push(n); if(!COST[n]) COST[n]={calls:0,prims:0}; COST[n].calls++; }
  function leave(){ STACK.pop(); }
  function tick(n){ if(STACK.length) COST[STACK[STACK.length-1]].prims += n; }
  function idx(x,y){ return (y|0)*W + (x|0); }
  function inb(x,y){ return x>=0&&x<W&&y>=0&&y<H; }

  /* ---- the five base ops ---- */
  function CLR(v){ grid.fill(v&IMAX); tick(1); }
  function PNT(x,y,w,h,v){ v&=IMAX;x|=0;y|=0;w|=0;h|=0;
    for(var j=0;j<h;j++){ var yy=y+j; if(yy<0||yy>=H) continue;
      for(var i=0;i<w;i++){ var xx=x+i; if(xx<0||xx>=W) continue; grid[idx(xx,yy)]=v; } } tick(1); }
  function LIN(x1,y1,x2,y2,v){ v&=IMAX;x1|=0;y1|=0;x2|=0;y2|=0;
    var dx=Math.abs(x2-x1),dy=-Math.abs(y2-y1),sx=x1<x2?1:-1,sy=y1<y2?1:-1,err=dx+dy;
    for(;;){ if(inb(x1,y1)) grid[idx(x1,y1)]=v; if(x1===x2&&y1===y2) break;
      var e2=2*err; if(e2>=dy){err+=dy;x1+=sx;} if(e2<=dx){err+=dx;y1+=sy;} } tick(1); }
  function SHF(dx,dy){ var out=new Uint8Array(W*H);dx|=0;dy|=0;
    for(var y=0;y<H;y++)for(var x=0;x<W;x++){ var sx=x-dx,sy=y-dy; out[idx(x,y)]=inb(sx,sy)?grid[idx(sx,sy)]:0; }
    grid.set(out); tick(1); }

  /* ============================================================
     TIER A — HOT PRIMITIVES (min prims; the frame budget)
     ============================================================ */
  function passage(x,y){ enter('passage'); PNT(x,y,8,12,0); PNT(x,y,8,1,7); LIN(x,y,x,y+12,5); leave(); }
  function rock(x,y,w,h){ enter('rock'); PNT(x,y,w,h,1);
    for(var i=0;i<w;i+=12) LIN(x+i,y,x+i,y+h,2); PNT(x,y,w,1,6); PNT(x,y,1,h,6); leave(); }
  function lampcone(x,y){ enter('lampcone'); // THE LEVERAGE ROUTINE: 3 prims over every lit frame
    PNT(x-6,y-2,12,6,1); PNT(x-12,y+4,24,8,1); PNT(x-20,y+12,40,10,1); leave(); }
  function figure(x,y,pose){ enter('figure');
    PNT(x-1,y-8,3,4,7); PNT(x-1,y-4,3,6,7);
    if(pose==='CLIMB'){ LIN(x-2,y-4,x-3,y-9,7);LIN(x+2,y-4,x+3,y-9,7);LIN(x-1,y+2,x-2,y-2,7);LIN(x+1,y+2,x+2,y-2,7); }
    else if(pose==='CROSS'){ LIN(x-1,y+2,x-4,y+6,7);LIN(x+1,y+2,x+4,y+5,7);LIN(x-2,y-3,x-6,y-4,7); }
    else if(pose==='DIG'){ LIN(x+1,y-3,x+8,y+2,7);LIN(x-1,y+2,x-3,y+7,7);LIN(x+1,y+2,x+2,y+7,7); }
    else { LIN(x-1,y+2,x-2,y+8,7);LIN(x+1,y+2,x+2,y+8,7);LIN(x-1,y-3,x-4,y-1,7); } leave(); }
  function glint(x,y){ enter('glint'); PNT(x,y,2,2,7); LIN(x-2,y,x+3,y,3); LIN(x,y-2,x,y+3,3); leave(); }

  /* shared mediums */
  function water(x,y,w,h,lvl){ enter('water'); PNT(x,y,w,h,lvl<1?1:lvl>4?4:lvl);
    for(var i=0;i<w;i+=4) LIN(x+i,y,x+i+2,y,6); leave(); }
  function haze(x,y,w,h,d){ enter('haze');
    for(var j=0;j<h;j+=d) for(var i=((j/d)&1?2:0);i<w;i+=d*2) PNT(x+i,y+j,1,1,3); leave(); }
  function shaft(x,y,depth){ enter('shaft'); PNT(x,y,10,depth,0); LIN(x,y,x,y+depth,6); LIN(x+10,y,x+10,y+depth,6); leave(); }

  /* ============================================================
     TIER B — PROPS (objects, drawn anywhere, state-parameterized)
     ============================================================ */
  function trapdoor(x,y,open){ enter('trapdoor');
    if(open){ PNT(x,y,16,3,0); LIN(x,y,x+16,y,7); PNT(x,y-6,16,3,7); }
    else { PNT(x,y,16,3,6); LIN(x,y,x+16,y,7); LIN(x,y+3,x+16,y+3,7); } leave(); }
  function rug(x,y){ enter('rug'); PNT(x,y,22,4,3); for(var i=0;i<22;i+=3) PNT(x+i,y,1,4,6); leave(); }
  function caseBox(x,y,filled){ enter('case');
    PNT(x,y,18,12,1); PNT(x,y,18,1,7); PNT(x,y+11,18,1,7); PNT(x,y,1,12,7); PNT(x+17,y,1,12,7);
    for(var s=0;s<filled&&s<3;s++) glint(x+4+s*5,y+5); leave(); }
  function bell(x,y){ enter('bell'); PNT(x,y,6,5,6); PNT(x+2,y+5,2,1,7); PNT(x+1,y-1,4,1,4); leave(); }
  function candle(x,y,lit){ enter('candle'); PNT(x,y,1,4,6); if(lit){ PNT(x,y-2,1,2,7); PNT(x-1,y-1,3,1,2);} leave(); }
  function rope(x,y,tied){ enter('rope'); if(tied){ LIN(x,y,x,y+24,5); PNT(x-1,y,3,1,7);} else { for(var i=0;i<5;i++) PNT(x+(i%2),y+i*2,2,2,5);} leave(); }
  function bolt(x,y,turned){ enter('bolt'); PNT(x,y,5,5,6); LIN(x,y,x+5,y+5,1); if(turned){ LIN(x,y+2,x+5,y+2,7);} else { LIN(x+2,y,x+2,y+5,7);} leave(); }
  function press(x,y,closed){ enter('press'); PNT(x,y,20,16,3); PNT(x,y,20,1,7); PNT(x+6,y-4,8,4,6); PNT(x+18,y+6,3,2,7);
    if(closed) PNT(x+2,y+13,16,2,7); else PNT(x+2,y+8,16,2,1); leave(); }
  function basket(x,y){ enter('basket'); LIN(x+5,y-8,x+5,y,4); PNT(x,y,10,5,2); PNT(x,y,10,1,7); PNT(x,y+4,10,1,7); leave(); }
  function nest(x,y,egg){ enter('nest'); PNT(x,y,10,4,4); for(var i=0;i<10;i+=2)PNT(x+i,y,1,4,6); if(egg){ PNT(x+3,y-3,4,4,5); PNT(x+4,y-3,2,1,7);} leave(); }
  function mailbox(x,y,open){ enter('mailbox'); PNT(x,y,7,5,6); LIN(x+3,y+5,x+3,y+9,5); if(open){ PNT(x+7,y,3,5,1); PNT(x+8,y+1,4,3,7);} leave(); }
  function buoy(x,y){ enter('buoy'); PNT(x,y,3,4,7); PNT(x-1,y+4,5,1,4); leave(); }
  function gratingBars(x,y,w,h){ enter('grating'); PNT(x,y,w,h,1); for(var i=0;i<w;i+=4) LIN(x+i,y,x+i,y+h,6); leave(); }

  /* ============================================================
     TIER C — AGENTS (the only movers; axis-state parameterized)
     ============================================================ */
  function troll(x,y,state){ enter('troll');
    if(state==='GONE'){ leave(); return; }
    if(state==='FALLING'){ PNT(x-6,y-4,14,14,7); LIN(x-8,y-6,x+12,y-14,6); LIN(x+12,y,x+20,y-4,2); LIN(x+12,y+4,x+22,y+2,2); }
    else { PNT(x-5,y-16,12,18,7); PNT(x-3,y-22,8,7,7); LIN(x-10,y-10,x+12,y-6,7); PNT(x+9,y-9,5,4,7); } leave(); }
  function cyclops(x,y,state){ enter('cyclops');
    if(state==='GONE'){ leave(); return; }
    if(state==='FLEEING'){ PNT(x-8,y-18,18,22,7); LIN(x+10,y-10,x+18,y-8,2); LIN(x+10,y,x+20,y+2,2);
      LIN(x+22,y-16,x+30,y-20,7); LIN(x+24,y-8,x+32,y-6,7); LIN(x+23,y,x+33,y+4,7); }
    else { PNT(x-10,y-16,22,20,7); PNT(x-2,y-10,3,3,0); } leave(); }
  function thief(x,y){ enter('thief'); PNT(x-2,y-12,5,14,7); LIN(x+3,y-8,x+9,y-12,7); glint(x+9,y-12); leave(); }
  function bat(x,y){ enter('bat'); PNT(x-1,y,3,2,7); LIN(x-1,y,x-7,y-3,6); LIN(x+2,y,x+8,y-3,6); leave(); }
  function spirits(x,y,w,h){ enter('spirits'); haze(x,y,w,h,4); leave(); }
  function grue(){ enter('grue'); CLR(7); leave(); }
  function hand(x,y){ enter('hand'); PNT(x-1,y,3,8,7); LIN(x-1,y-2,x-3,y-4,7); LIN(x+1,y-2,x+3,y-4,7); LIN(x,y-2,x,y-5,7); leave(); }

  /* ============================================================
     TIER D — PLATES (rooms = compositions; heavy ones detailed)
     ============================================================ */
  var _roundCache = null;
  function plate_round_room(){ enter('plate_round_room');
    if(_roundCache){ grid.set(_roundCache); tick(1); leave(); return; } // CACHED recall
    CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H);
    var cx=64,cy=48,spokes=[[64,4],[104,12],[112,44],[104,76],[64,84],[24,76],[16,44],[24,12]];
    for(var k=0;k<spokes.length;k++){ passage(spokes[k][0]-4,spokes[k][1]); LIN(cx,cy,spokes[k][0],spokes[k][1]+6,3); }
    PNT(cx-12,cy-12,24,24,1); LIN(cx-12,cy-12,cx+12,cy-12,6); LIN(cx-12,cy+12,cx+12,cy+12,6);
    _roundCache = grid.slice(); leave(); }
  function plate_aragain(){ enter('plate_aragain'); CLR(0); rock(0,60,W,36);
    for(var i=40;i<88;i+=2) LIN(i,0,i-4,60,5);
    for(var r=0;r<5;r++){ var yy=18+r*3; for(var x=18;x<110;x+=3) PNT(x, yy-Math.round(8*Math.sin((x-18)/92*Math.PI)),1,1,6-r); }
    PNT(0,72,128,24,0); LIN(0,72,128,72,6); leave(); }
  function plate_hades(){ enter('plate_hades'); CLR(0); haze(0,0,W,H,5);
    PNT(38,24,6,56,6); PNT(84,24,6,56,6); PNT(38,24,52,6,6);
    for(var i=0;i<5;i++){ PNT(40,32+i*9,2,6,7); PNT(86,32+i*9,2,6,7); } glint(64,52); PNT(62,48,5,5,5); leave(); }
  function plate_dam(){ enter('plate_dam'); CLR(0); water(0,0,W,22,3); rock(0,22,W,12);
    PNT(20,40,40,28,2); PNT(20,40,40,1,7); PNT(20,67,40,1,7);
    for(var i=0;i<3;i++)for(var j=0;j<2;j++) glint(30+i*12,48+j*10);
    bolt(96,46,false); PNT(0,80,128,16,1); for(var s=0;s<128;s+=10) PNT(s,80,2,16,5); leave(); }
  function plate_machine_room(){ enter('plate_machine_room'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H); press(54,44,false); passage(8,52); passage(112,52); leave(); }
  function plate_temple(){ enter('plate_temple'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H);
    PNT(40,64,48,8,3); PNT(48,56,32,8,3); PNT(56,48,16,8,3); bell(58,36); candle(46,54,false); candle(80,54,false); passage(8,40); passage(112,40); leave(); }
  /* lighter plates */
  function plate_west_house(){ enter('plate_west_house'); CLR(0);
    PNT(28,30,72,50,1); PNT(28,30,72,1,7); PNT(28,79,72,1,7); PNT(28,30,1,50,7); PNT(99,30,1,50,7);
    LIN(40,42,84,42,7); LIN(40,42,62,30,7); LIN(84,42,62,30,7);
    PNT(56,52,16,28,3); LIN(56,52,84,80,1); LIN(72,52,56,80,1);
    for(var i=0;i<W;i+=5) PNT(i,84,2,12,4); mailbox(14,68,false); leave(); }
  function plate_forest(){ enter('plate_forest'); CLR(0); for(var i=8;i<W;i+=18) PNT(i,10,3,86,5); PNT(0,88,W,8,1); leave(); }
  function plate_clearing(){ enter('plate_clearing'); CLR(0); for(var i=0;i<W;i+=22) PNT(i,8,3,40,5); gratingBars(48,60,32,24); LIN(64,60,64,96,2); leave(); }
  function plate_living_room(){ enter('plate_living_room'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H); caseBox(20,18,0); rug(50,66); trapdoor(52,72,false); passage(104,40); leave(); }
  function plate_kitchen(){ enter('plate_kitchen'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H);
    PNT(40,60,40,4,3); PNT(48,52,6,8,5); PNT(64,50,4,10,5); PNT(96,8,16,40,0); LIN(96,8,96,48,6); LIN(112,8,112,48,6); PNT(20,30,12,16,1); leave(); }
  function plate_attic(){ enter('plate_attic'); CLR(0); PNT(0,0,W,H,2); LIN(0,20,W,40,7); rope(24,46,false); LIN(70,56,96,52,6); glint(96,52); leave(); }
  function plate_cellar(){ enter('plate_cellar'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H); trapdoor(56,8,true); passage(104,52); leave(); }
  function plate_troll_room(){ enter('plate_troll_room'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H); PNT(20,80,88,8,4); passage(8,40); passage(60,38); passage(112,40); leave(); }
  function plate_maze(){ enter('plate_maze'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H); passage(8,30); passage(56,50); passage(108,28); glint(40,82); glint(70,80); leave(); }
  function plate_cyclops_room(){ enter('plate_cyclops_room'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H); for(var i=0;i<6;i++) LIN(90,72-i*10,110,66-i*10,5); leave(); }
  function plate_grating_room(){ enter('plate_grating_room'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H); gratingBars(40,12,40,16); LIN(60,28,60,40,2); glint(64,70); leave(); }
  function plate_dome_room(){ enter('plate_dome_room'); CLR(0); PNT(0,60,W,36,0); for(var i=0;i<W;i+=10) PNT(i,52,3,8,6); LIN(0,52,W,52,7); rope(64,52,false); leave(); }
  function plate_reservoir(){ enter('plate_reservoir'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,14); water(0,14,W,70,3); PNT(0,84,W,12,2); leave(); }
  function plate_frigid_river(){ enter('plate_frigid_river'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,16); rock(0,78,W,18); water(0,16,W,62,2); for(var i=0;i<W;i+=6) LIN(i,40,i+8,40,5); buoy(70,44); leave(); }
  function plate_gas_room(){ enter('plate_gas_room'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H); haze(0,0,W,H,8); glint(60,70); leave(); }
  function plate_coal_mine(){ enter('plate_coal_mine'); CLR(0); PNT(0,0,W,H,3); passage(20,40); passage(80,30); passage(50,60); leave(); }
  function plate_shaft_room(){ enter('plate_shaft_room'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H); shaft(58,30,60); basket(56,28); leave(); }
  function plate_loud_room(){ enter('plate_loud_room'); CLR(0); rock(0,0,W,H);
    for(var i=0;i<5;i++){ LIN(20,48,40-i*4,30-i*6,4); LIN(108,48,88+i*4,30-i*6,4); } PNT(60,60,8,6,7); glint(64,52); passage(8,40); passage(112,40); leave(); }

  /* ============================================================
     PART 3 — PROGRAMS (one per state unit; functions of the axes)
     Each reads the live axes so ONE program renders every state.
     ============================================================ */
  var PROGS = {

    su_surface_house: function(S){
      if(S.descended){ plate_cellar(); if(S.lit) lampcone(64,60); figure(64,62,'STAND'); return ['C descended','plate_cellar','trapdoor -> sealed']; }
      plate_west_house(); if(S.opened) mailbox(14,68,true); figure(60,80,'STAND');
      return ['plate_west_house', S.opened?'mailbox 14 68 OPEN':'C mailbox closed','figure 60 80 STAND']; },

    su_light_darkness: function(S){
      if(!S.lit){ if(S.grue){ grue(); return ['C SEAM: grue death','CLR 7']; }
        CLR(7); PNT(62,46,2,2,0); PNT(60,48,1,1,0); PNT(66,46,1,1,0); return ['C DARK: room erased','CLR 7','C located disturbance']; }
      plate_troll_room(); figure(30,72,'STAND'); lampcone(30,70);
      return ['plate_troll_room (any lit room)','figure 30 72','lampcone 30 70  C the leverage routine']; },

    su_troll_gate: function(S){
      plate_troll_room();
      var st = S.troll || 'BARS'; troll(64,70,st); figure(24,72,'STAND'); if(S.lit) lampcone(24,70);
      return ['plate_troll_room','troll 64 70 '+st, st==='FALLING'?'C SEAM: troll slain':'C blocking','figure 24 72']; },

    su_maze_grating: function(S){
      if(S.gratingOpen){ plate_grating_room(); if(S.lit) lampcone(64,60); return ['plate_grating_room','grating -> open (shortcut)']; }
      plate_maze(); for(var i=0;i<4;i++) glint(20+i*22,86); figure(30,60,'STAND'); if(S.lit) lampcone(30,58);
      return ['plate_maze','C dropped objects as markers','figure 30 60']; },

    su_cyclops_gate: function(S){
      plate_cyclops_room(); var st=S.cyclops||'SLEEP'; cyclops(70,60,st); figure(20,64,'STAND'); if(S.lit) lampcone(20,62);
      return ['plate_cyclops_room','cyclops 70 60 '+st, st==='FLEEING'?'C SEAM: word breaks wall':'C asleep','figure 20 64']; },

    su_thief_economy: function(S){
      plate_maze(); if(S.thiefDead){ figure(60,60,'STAND'); for(var i=0;i<3;i++) glint(40+i*16,40); }
      else { thief(80,60); figure(30,60,'STAND'); } if(S.lit) lampcone(S.thiefDead?60:30,58);
      return ['plate_maze', S.thiefDead?'C thief defeated, treasure recovered':'thief 80 60  C one routine, any room']; },

    su_egg_canary_bauble: function(S){
      if(S.bauble){ plate_forest(); glint(64,70); figure(40,80,'STAND'); return ['plate_forest','C canary wound -> bauble falls','glint 64 70']; }
      plate_maze(); nest(58,40,!S.eggOpen); if(S.eggOpen) thief(50,55); if(S.lit) lampcone(80,58);
      return ['C up-tree egg / treasure room','nest 58 40 '+(S.eggOpen?'EMPTY':'EGG'), S.eggOpen?'thief opens it (delegation)':'C cannot open safely']; },

    su_temple_hades: function(S){
      if(S.exorcised){ plate_hades(); hand(64,70); if(S.lit) lampcone(64,60); return ['C SEAM: exorcised','plate_hades','hand 64 70  C take skull']; }
      plate_temple(); if(S.ritual){ candle(46,54,true); candle(80,54,true); glint(58,30); } figure(100,46,'STAND'); if(S.lit) lampcone(100,44);
      return ['plate_temple', S.ritual?'candle LIT x2  C bell+book+candle':'C ritual not begun','figure 100 46']; },

    su_dam_reservoir: function(S){
      plate_dam(); if(S.drained){ bolt(96,46,true); PNT(0,80,128,16,0); } figure(12,60,'STAND'); if(S.lit) lampcone(12,58);
      return ['plate_dam','bolt 96 46 '+(S.drained?'TURNED':'closed'), S.drained?'C SEAM: reservoir drained':'C water held','figure 12 60']; },

    su_river_rainbow: function(S){
      if(S.rainbow){ plate_aragain(); PNT(96,30,8,8,7); glint(100,34); figure(20,64,'STAND'); return ['C SEAM: rainbow solid','plate_aragain','C pot of gold appears']; }
      plate_frigid_river(); figure(64,46,'CROSS'); if(S.lit) lampcone(64,40);
      return ['plate_frigid_river','figure 64 46 CROSS  C in the boat','buoy 70 44']; },

    su_mine_gas_basket: function(S){
      plate_gas_room(); if(!S.batRepelled) bat(80,30); hand(60,68); figure(30,72,'CROSS'); if(S.lit) lampcone(30,68);
      return ['plate_gas_room', S.batRepelled?'C garlic carried, bat gone':'bat 80 30  C abducts','hand 60 68  C sapphire, lamp only','figure 30 72 CROSS']; },

    su_machine_diamond: function(S){
      plate_machine_room(); press(54,44,!!S.pressed); if(S.pressed) glint(64,52); figure(20,60,'STAND'); if(S.lit) lampcone(20,58);
      return ['plate_machine_room','press 54 44 '+(S.pressed?'CLOSED':'open'), S.pressed?'C SEAM: coal -> diamond':'C coal in hopper','figure 20 60']; },

    su_loud_room: function(S){
      plate_loud_room(); if(S.quiet){ /* echo-lines suppressed by plate state */ glint(64,52); hand(60,64); } figure(24,64,'STAND'); if(S.lit) lampcone(24,62);
      return ['plate_loud_room', S.quiet?'C said ECHO -> room quiets':'C commands echo','C platinum bar', S.quiet?'hand 60 64  C take bar':'']; },

    su_trophy_endgame: function(S){
      plate_living_room();
      var f = S.full ? 3 : (S.deposited||1);
      caseBox(20,18,f);
      if(S.full){ PNT(50,60,28,20,1); LIN(50,60,78,80,6); LIN(78,60,50,80,6); }
      hand(24,30); figure(90,60,'STAND'); if(S.lit) lampcone(90,58);
      return ['plate_living_room','case -> '+f+'/3 filled', S.full?'C WIN: Stone Barrow map':'C deposit a treasure','hand 24 30']; }
  };

  /* ============================================================
     PART 4 — RENDER + STATE
     ============================================================ */
  // default axis state per unit (the "present" first-look)
  var DEFAULTS = {
    su_surface_house:   { lit:true, opened:false, descended:false },
    su_light_darkness:  { lit:true, grue:false },
    su_troll_gate:      { lit:true, troll:'BARS' },
    su_maze_grating:    { lit:true, gratingOpen:false },
    su_cyclops_gate:    { lit:true, cyclops:'SLEEP' },
    su_thief_economy:   { lit:true, thiefDead:false },
    su_egg_canary_bauble:{ lit:true, eggOpen:false, bauble:false },
    su_temple_hades:    { lit:true, ritual:false, exorcised:false },
    su_dam_reservoir:   { lit:true, drained:false },
    su_river_rainbow:   { lit:true, rainbow:false },
    su_mine_gas_basket: { lit:true, batRepelled:false },
    su_machine_diamond: { lit:true, pressed:false },
    su_loud_room:       { lit:true, quiet:false },
    su_trophy_endgame:  { lit:true, deposited:1, full:false }
  };
  // toggle definitions per unit: [label, axisKey, valueWhenOn, valueWhenOff]
  var TOGGLES = {
    su_surface_house:   [['LIT','lit',true,false],['OPEN MAIL','opened',true,false],['DESCEND','descended',true,false]],
    su_light_darkness:  [['LIT','lit',true,false],['GRUE','grue',true,false]],
    su_troll_gate:      [['LIT','lit',true,false],['SLAY','troll','FALLING','BARS']],
    su_maze_grating:    [['LIT','lit',true,false],['OPEN GRATE','gratingOpen',true,false]],
    su_cyclops_gate:    [['LIT','lit',true,false],['SAY NAME','cyclops','FLEEING','SLEEP']],
    su_thief_economy:   [['LIT','lit',true,false],['KILL THIEF','thiefDead',true,false]],
    su_egg_canary_bauble:[['LIT','lit',true,false],['EGG OPEN','eggOpen',true,false],['BAUBLE','bauble',true,false]],
    su_temple_hades:    [['LIT','lit',true,false],['RITUAL','ritual',true,false],['EXORCISE','exorcised',true,false]],
    su_dam_reservoir:   [['LIT','lit',true,false],['DRAIN','drained',true,false]],
    su_river_rainbow:   [['LIT','lit',true,false],['RAINBOW','rainbow',true,false]],
    su_mine_gas_basket: [['LIT','lit',true,false],['GARLIC','batRepelled',true,false]],
    su_machine_diamond: [['LIT','lit',true,false],['PRESS','pressed',true,false]],
    su_loud_room:       [['LIT','lit',true,false],['ECHO','quiet',true,false]],
    su_trophy_endgame:  [['LIT','lit',true,false],['FILL CASE','full',true,false]]
  };

  function renderTo(canvas, prog, S){
    for(var k in COST) delete COST[k];
    STACK.length = 0;
    grid.fill(0);
    var code = prog(S) || [];
    // paint to canvas: intensity -> dot size (Knowlton halftone)
    var ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
    var scale = canvas._scale || 4;
    ctx.fillStyle = '#fff'; ctx.fillRect(0,0,canvas.width,canvas.height);
    ctx.fillStyle = '#000';
    for(var y=0;y<H;y++) for(var x=0;x<W;x++){
      var v = grid[idx(x,y)]; if(!v) continue;
      var frac = v/IMAX, d = Math.max(1, Math.round(scale*frac)), off = Math.floor((scale-d)/2);
      ctx.fillRect(x*scale+off, y*scale+off, d, d);
    }
    return code;
  }

  function codeHTML(lines){
    return lines.filter(function(L){return L;}).map(function(L){
      if(L.indexOf('C ')===0) return '<span class="c">'+esc(L)+'</span>';
      var sp = L.indexOf(' ');
      if(sp>0) return '<span class="k">'+esc(L.slice(0,sp))+'</span>'+esc(L.slice(sp));
      return '<span class="k">'+esc(L)+'</span>';
    }).join('\n');
  }
  function esc(s){ return s.replace(/&/g,'&amp;').replace(/</g,'&lt;').replace(/>/g,'&gt;'); }

  /* ============================================================
     PART 5 — MOUNT into each passage that carries a stage
     Harlowe renders passages; we scan for our marker and build the
     canvas + toggle bar + live code readout, wired to the axes.
     ============================================================ */
  function mountStages(root){
    var stages = (root||document).querySelectorAll('.beflix-stage[data-prog]');
    for(var i=0;i<stages.length;i++){ buildStage(stages[i]); }
  }
  function buildStage(stage){
    if(stage._built) return; stage._built = true;
    var progId = stage.getAttribute('data-prog');
    var prog = PROGS[progId]; if(!prog){ stage.textContent = '[no BEFLIX program: '+progId+']'; return; }
    var S = {}; var d = DEFAULTS[progId]||{}; for(var k in d) S[k]=d[k];

    var scale = 4;
    var canvas = document.createElement('canvas');
    canvas.width = W*scale; canvas.height = H*scale; canvas._scale = scale;
    stage.appendChild(canvas);

    var bar = document.createElement('div'); bar.className='beflix-bar';
    var caption = document.createElement('div'); caption.className='beflix-cap';
    var codeEl = document.createElement('div'); codeEl.className='beflix-code';

    function paint(){
      var code = renderTo(canvas, prog, S);
      codeEl.innerHTML = codeHTML(code);
      // cost summary in the caption
      var tc=0,tp=0,n=0; for(var k in COST){ tc+=COST[k].calls; tp+=COST[k].prims; n++; }
      caption.textContent = n+' routines · '+tc+' calls · '+tp+' prims  —  same program, every state';
    }
    var toggles = TOGGLES[progId]||[['LIT','lit',true,false]];
    for(var t=0;t<toggles.length;t++){
      (function(def){
        var btn = document.createElement('button');
        btn.textContent = def[0];
        function sync(){ var on = (S[def[1]]===def[2]); btn.setAttribute('data-on', on?'1':'0'); }
        btn.addEventListener('click', function(){
          var on = (S[def[1]]===def[2]);
          S[def[1]] = on ? def[3] : def[2];
          sync(); paint();
        });
        sync();
        bar.appendChild(btn);
      })(toggles[t]);
    }
    stage.appendChild(bar);
    stage.appendChild(caption);
    stage.appendChild(codeEl);
    paint();
  }

  // Harlowe fires 'showpassage' style hooks via DOM mutation; observe and mount.
  function boot(){
    mountStages(document);
    var mo = new MutationObserver(function(muts){
      for(var i=0;i<muts.length;i++){
        var m = muts[i];
        for(var j=0;j<m.addedNodes.length;j++){
          var n = m.addedNodes[j];
          if(n.nodeType===1){ if(n.matches&&n.matches('.beflix-stage[data-prog]')) buildStage(n); mountStages(n); }
        }
      }
    });
    mo.observe(document.body, {childList:true, subtree:true});
  }
  if(document.readyState!=='loading') boot();
  else document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', boot);

  // expose for debugging / external drive
  window.ZBEFLIX = { PROGS:PROGS, render:renderTo, grid:function(){return grid;}, COST:COST };
})();

:: Start [index] {"position":"0,0","size":"180,120"}
# ZORK I LEGOS STATEGRAPH · BEFLIX

This Twee file turns the Zork LEGOS decomposition into a loadable Twine graph, with a live BEFLIX-128 engine embedded.

The rule holds: do not bake twenty-one CINEOSIS images for every atom. Load the atoms, select a state unit. The BEFLIX engine renders that unit — and every state of its rooms — from ONE program that reads the state axes. Coded images, not baked frames.

<div class="legos-card">
Core path:

* [[State Units]]
* [[Atom Index]]
* [[Timeline Phases]]
* [[Engine Contract]]
* [[BEFLIX Engine]]
* [[Validator Checklist]]
* [[LEGOS Engine JSON]]
</div>

Start the playable/filmable chain here: [[SU 01 Surface House]]

:: Engine Contract [index] {"position":"220,0","size":"180,120"}
# Engine Contract

The engine consumes a selected `state_unit`, not the whole document.

Each state unit carries:

* LEGOS atom references.
* A PAST state.
* A PRESENT action.
* A FUTURE consequence.
* An ABC CINEOSIS seed.
* A BEFLIX PROGRAM — a function of the state axes.

The BEFLIX program is the executable form of PAST/PRESENT/FUTURE: flip an axis (LIT->DARK, troll BARS->FALLING, reservoir held->drained) and the SAME program renders the new state. No baked frames.

The engine then expands a selected unit into:

* premise · temporal engine · ABC model
* 21-image matrix · shot sequence
* sound map · edit map
* BEFLIX (already live below each unit)

[[Start]] · [[BEFLIX Engine]]

:: BEFLIX Engine [index beflix] {"position":"440,0","size":"200,140"}
# BEFLIX Engine

The interpreter lives once in `StoryJavaScript`. It is a real BEFLIX-128 machine: a 128×96 grid, the five base ops (`CLR`/`PNT`/`LIN`/`SHF` + render), and a routine library in cost tiers.

<div class="legos-card">
**Cost discipline (baked in):**

* HOT primitives — `passage`, `rock`, `lampcone`, `figure`, `glint` — stripped to minimum prims. They are the frame budget.
* HEAVY plates — `round_room`, `aragain`, `hades`, `dam` — full detail, called rarely.
* `round_room` is CACHED: built once, recalled cheap. The one hot-and-heavy routine.
* `lampcone` is the leverage routine: 3 prims layered over every lit frame. LIT draws it; DARK is `CLR 7` — free.
</div>

Every state unit below carries a live stage. Use the buttons to flip the state axes and watch one program render every state. The caption shows the measured routine/call/prim cost for the current frame.

